files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IDropProcessor
files.Summary: Drops the document without raising any errors. This is useful to prevent the document from getting indexed based on some condition.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IDynamicTemplate
files.Summary:
A Dynamic template that defines custom mappings to be applied to dynamically added fields based on:

- the datatype detected by OpenSearch, with .

- the name of the field, with and or .

- the full dotted path to the field, with and .

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IEdgeNGramTokenFilter
files.Summary: A token filter of type edgeNGram.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IElisionTokenFilter
files.Summary: A token filter which removes elisions. For example, lavion (the plane) will tokenized as avion (plane).

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IExecutePainlessScriptRequest
files.Summary: The Painless execute API allows an arbitrary script to be executed and a result to be returned.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IFailProcessor
files.Summary: Raises an exception. This is useful for when you expect a pipeline to fail and want to relay a specific message to the requester.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IFieldAliasProperty
files.Summary: An alias mapping defines an alternate name for a field in the index. The alias can be used in place of the target field in search requests, and selected other APIs like field capabilities.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IFieldCollapse
files.Summary:
Allows to collapse search results based on field values. The collapsing is done by selecting only the top sorted document per collapse key. For instance the query below retrieves the best tweet for each user and sorts them by number of likes.

NOTE: The collapsing is applied to the top hits only and does not affect aggregations.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IFieldMapping
files.Summary: A document field mapping in OpenSearch

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IFileSystemRepository
files.Summary: A snapshot repository that uses a shared file system to store snapshot data. The path specified in the location parameter should point to the same location in the shared filesystem and be accessible on all data and cluster_manager nodes.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IFingerprintAnalyzer
files.Summary: The fingerprint analyzer implements a fingerprinting algorithm which is used by the OpenRefine project to assist in clustering.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IFingerprintTokenFilter
files.Summary: The fingerprint token filter emits a single token which is useful for fingerprinting a body of text, and/or providing a token that can be clustered on. It does this by sorting the tokens, deduplicating and then concatenating them back into a single token.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IFloatRangeProperty
files.Summary: A range of single-precision 32-bit IEEE 754 floating point values.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IForeachProcessor
files.Summary: Processes elements in an array of unknown length. All processors can operate on elements inside an array, but if all elements of an array need to be processed in the same way, defining a processor for each element becomes cumbersome and tricky because it is likely that the number of elements in an array is unknown. For this reason the foreach processor exists. By specifying the field holding array elements and a processor that defines what should happen to each element, array fields can easily be preprocessed.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IFormattableMetricAggregation
files.Summary: A metric aggregation that can accept a format to use for the output of the aggregation

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IGenericProperty
files.Summary: A generic property to map properties that may be of different types. Not all methods are valid for all types.

files.Summary: Allows you to sort based on a proximity to one or more

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IGeoHashGridAggregation
files.Summary: A multi-bucket aggregation that works on geo_point fields and groups points into buckets that represent cells in a grid. The resulting grid can be sparse and only contains cells that have matching data. Each cell is labeled using a geohash which is of user-definable precision.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IGeoIpProcessor
files.Summary: The GeoIP processor adds information about the geographical location of IP addresses, based on data from the Maxmind databases. This processor adds this information by default under the geoip field. The geoip processor can resolve both IPv4 and IPv6 addresses.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IGeoPointProperty
files.Summary: Data type mapping to map a property as a geopoint

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IGeoShapeProperty
files.Summary: Maps a property as a geo_shape field

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IGeoTileGridCompositeAggregationSource
files.Summary: A values source that is equivalent to a simple Geo aggregation.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IGeometryCollection
files.Summary: A geo shape representing a collection of geometries

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IGsubProcessor
files.Summary: Converts a string field by applying a regular expression and a replacement. If the field is not a string, the processor will throw an exception.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IHdfsRepository
files.Summary:
A snapshot repository that stores snapshot data within a Hadoop HDFS filesystem

Requires the repository-hdfs plugin to be installed on the cluster

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IHistogramCompositeAggregationSource
files.Summary: A value source that can be applied on numeric values to build fixed size interval over the values. The interval parameter defines how the numeric values should be transformed. For instance an interval set to 5 will translate any numeric values to its closest interval, a value of 101 would be translated to 100 which is the key for the interval between 100 and 105.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IHitMetadata<TDocument>
files.Summary: Metadata about a hit matching a query

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IHtmlStripCharFilter
files.Summary: A char filter of type html_strip stripping out HTML elements from an analyzed text.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IHunspellTokenFilter
files.Summary:
Basic support for hunspell stemming.

Hunspell dictionaries will be picked up from a dedicated hunspell directory on the filesystem.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IHyphenationDecompounderTokenFilter
files.Summary: Token filters that allow to decompose compound words.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIBSimilarity
files.Summary: Information based model similarity. The algorithm is based on the concept that the information content in any symbolic distribution sequence is primarily determined by the repetitive usage of its basic elements. For written texts this challenge would correspond to comparing the writing styles of different authors.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIcuAnalyzer
files.Summary: An ICU analyzer that performs basic normalization, tokenization and character folding, using the char filter, and token filter

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIcuCollationTokenFilter
files.Summary: Collations are used for sorting documents in a language-specific word order. The icu_collation token filter is available to all indices and defaults to using the DUCET collation, which is a best-effort attempt at language-neutral sorting. Part of the analysis-icu plugin:

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIcuFoldingTokenFilter
files.Summary: Case folding of Unicode characters based on UTR#30, like the ASCII-folding token filter on steroids.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIcuTokenizer
files.Summary: Tokenizes text into words on word boundaries, as defined in UAX #29: Unicode Text Segmentation. It behaves much like the standard tokenizer, but adds better support for some Asian languages by using a dictionary-based approach to identify words in Thai, Lao, Chinese, Japanese, and Korean, and using custom rules to break Myanmar and Khmer text into syllables.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIcuTransformTokenFilter
files.Summary: Transforms are used to process Unicode text in many different ways, such as case mapping, normalization, transliteration and bidirectional text handling.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIndicesModuleSettings
files.Summary: Settings to control where, when, and how shards are allocated to nodes.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIntegerRangeProperty
files.Summary: A range of signed 32-bit integers with a minimum value of -231 and maximum of 231-1.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIntervals
files.Summary: An rule with an optional filter

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIntervalsAllOf
files.Summary: A rule that returns matches that span a combination of other rules.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIntervalsAnyOf
files.Summary: A rule that emits intervals produced by any of its sub-rules.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIntervalsFilter
files.Summary: Filters intervals produced by any rules by their relation to the intervals produced by another rule

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIntervalsFuzzy
files.Summary: The fuzzy rule matches terms that are similar to the provided term, within an edit distance defined by Fuzziness. If the fuzzy expansion matches more than 128 terms, OpenSearch returns an error.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIntervalsPrefix
files.Summary: Matches terms that start with a specified set of characters. This prefix can expand to match at most 128 terms. If the prefix matches more than 128 terms, OpenSearch returns an error. You can use the index-prefixes option in the field mapping to avoid this limit.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIntervalsQuery
files.Summary: A query that allows fine-grained control over the order and proximity of matching terms. Matching rules are constructed from a small set of definitions, and the rules are then applied to terms from a particular field. The definitions produce sequences of minimal intervals that span terms in a body of text. These intervals can be further combined and filtered by parent sources.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIntervalsWildcard
files.Summary: Matches terms using a wildcard pattern. This pattern can expand to match at most 128 terms. If the pattern matches more than 128 terms, OpenSearch returns an error.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIpProperty
files.Summary: An ip field can index/store either IPv4 or IPv6 addresses.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IIpRangeProperty
files.Summary: A range of ip values supporting either IPv4 or IPv6 (or mixed) addresses.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IJoinProcessor
files.Summary: Joins each element of an array into a single string using a separator character between each element. Throws an error when the field is not an array.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IJoinProperty
files.Summary: The join datatype is a special field that creates parent/child relation within documents of the same index.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IJsonProcessor
files.Summary: Converts a JSON string into a structured JSON object.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IKStemTokenFilter
files.Summary:
The kstem token filter is a high performance filter for english.

All terms must already be lowercased (use lowercase filter) for this filter to work correctly.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IKeepTypesTokenFilter
files.Summary: A token filter of type keep that only keeps tokens with text contained in a predefined set of words.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IKeepWordsTokenFilter
files.Summary: A token filter of type keep that only keeps tokens with text contained in a predefined set of words.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IKeyValueProcessor
files.Summary: Processor to automatically parse messages (or specific event fields) which are of the key=value variety.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IKeywordAnalyzer
files.Summary:
An analyzer of type keyword that tokenizes an entire stream as a single token. This is useful for data like zip codes, ids and so on.

Note, when using mapping definitions, it make more sense to simply mark the field as not_analyzed.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IKeywordMarkerTokenFilter
files.Summary: Protects words from being modified by stemmers. Must be placed before any stemming filters.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IKeywordProperty
files.Summary:
A field to index structured content such as IDs, email addresses, hostnames, status codes, zip codes or tags. Used for filtering, sorting, and for aggregations.

Keyword fields are only searchable by their exact value.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IKeywordTokenizer
files.Summary: A tokenizer of type keyword that emits the entire input as a single input.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IKuromojiAnalyzer
files.Summary: An analyzer tailored for japanese that is bootstrapped with defaults. Part of the analysis-kuromoji plugin:

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IKuromojiIterationMarkCharFilter
files.Summary: The kuromoji_iteration_mark normalizes Japanese horizontal iteration marks (odoriji) to their expanded form. Part of the analysis-kuromoji plugin:

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IKuromojiPartOfSpeechTokenFilter
files.Summary: The kuromoji_part_of_speech token filter removes tokens that match a set of part-of-speech tags. Part of the analysis-kuromoji plugin:

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IKuromojiReadingFormTokenFilter
files.Summary: The kuromoji_readingform token filter replaces the token with its reading form in either katakana or romaji. Part of the analysis-kuromoji plugin:

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IKuromojiStemmerTokenFilter
files.Summary: The kuromoji_stemmer token filter normalizes common katakana spelling variations ending in a long sound character by removing this character (U+30FC). Only full-width katakana characters are supported. Part of the analysis-kuromoji plugin:

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IKuromojiTokenizer
files.Summary: A tokenizer of type pattern that can flexibly separate text into terms via a regular expression. Part of the analysis-kuromoji plugin:

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ILMDirichletSimilarity
files.Summary: A similarity with Bayesian smoothing using Dirichlet priors.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ILMJelinekMercerSimilarity
files.Summary: A similarity that attempts to capture important patterns in the text, while leaving out noise.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ILanguageAnalyzer
files.Summary: A set of analyzers aimed at analyzing specific language text.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ILengthTokenFilter
files.Summary: A token filter of type length that removes words that are too long or too short for the stream.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ILetterTokenizer
files.Summary:
A tokenizer of type letter that divides text at non-letters. Thats to say, it defines tokens as maximal strings of adjacent letters.

Note, this does a decent job for most European languages, but does a terrible job for some Asian languages, where words are not separated by spaces.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ILikeDocument
files.Summary: An indexed or artificial document with which to find likeness

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ILimitTokenCountTokenFilter
files.Summary: Limits the number of tokens that are indexed per document and field.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ILongRangeProperty
files.Summary: A range of signed 64-bit integers with a minimum value of -263 and maximum of 263-1.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ILowercaseProcessor
files.Summary: Converts a string to its lowercase equivalent.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ILowercaseTokenFilter
files.Summary:
A token filter of type lowercase that normalizes token text to lower case.

Lowercase token filter supports Greek and Turkish lowercase token filters through the language parameter.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ILowercaseTokenizer
files.Summary:
A tokenizer of type lowercase that performs the function of Letter Tokenizer and Lower Case Token Filter together.

It divides text at non-letters and converts them to lower case.

While it is functionally equivalent to the combination of Letter Tokenizer and Lower Case Token Filter,

there is a performance advantage to doing the two tasks at once, hence this (redundant) implementation.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IMappingCharFilter
files.Summary: A char filter of type mapping replacing characters of an analyzed text with given mapping.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IMatchBoolPrefixQuery
files.Summary: A match_bool_prefix query analyzes its input and constructs a bool query from the terms. Each term except the last is used in a term query. The last term is used in a prefix query.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IMatchQuery
files.Summary: A match query for a single field

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IMedianAbsoluteDeviationAggregation
files.Summary:
This single-value aggregation approximates the median absolute deviation of its search results.

Median absolute deviation is a measure of variability. It is a robust statistic, meaning that it is useful for describing data that may have outliers, or may not be normally distributed. For such data it can be more descriptive than standard deviation.

It is calculated as the median of each data points deviation from the median of the entire sample. That is, for a random variable 

X
, the median absolute deviation is 
median(|median(X) - Xi|).

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IMetricAggregation
files.Summary: An aggregation that computes metrics based on values extracted in one way or another from the documents that are being aggregated.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IMultiMatchQuery
files.Summary: A match query across multiple fields.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IMultiTermVectorOperation
files.Summary: An operation to define the calculation of term vectors when using Multi termvectors API

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IMultiplexerTokenFilter
files.Summary: A token filter of type multiplexer will emit multiple tokens at the same position, each version of the token having been run through a different filter. Identical output tokens at the same position will be removed.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.INGramTokenFilter
files.Summary: A token filter of type nGram.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.INestedProperty
files.Summary: A specialised version of the datatype that allows arrays of objects to be indexed in a way that they can be queried independently of each other, using nested queries and aggregations.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.INestedSort
files.Summary: Sort on a field inside one or more nested objects.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.INoriAnalyzer
files.Summary:
The nori analyzer consists of the following tokenizer and token filters:

- nori_tokenizer

- nori_part_of_speech token filter

- nori_readingform token filter

- nori_number token filter

- lowercase token filter

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.INoriPartOfSpeechTokenFilter
files.Summary: The nori_part_of_speech token filter removes tokens that match a set of part-of-speech tags.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.INoriTokenizer
files.Summary: Tokenizer that ships with the analysis-nori plugin

files.Summary: A numeric mapping that defaults to float.

files.Summary: Sets up contextual scope for the painless script the execute under.

files.Summary: A special single bucket aggregation that selects parent documents that have the specified type, as defined in a join field.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IParentIdQuery
files.Summary: The parent_id query can be used to find child documents which belong to a particular parent.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IPathHierarchyTokenizer
files.Summary:
The path_hierarchy tokenizer takes something like this:

/something/something/else

And produces tokens:

/something

/something/something

/something/something/else

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IPatternAnalyzer
files.Summary: An analyzer of type pattern that can flexibly separate text into terms via a regular expression.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IPatternCaptureTokenFilter
files.Summary: The pattern_capture token filter, unlike the pattern tokenizer, emits a token for every capture group in the regular expression.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IPatternReplaceCharFilter
files.Summary: The pattern_replace char filter allows the use of a regex to manipulate the characters in a string before analysis.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IPatternReplaceTokenFilter
files.Summary: The pattern_replace token filter allows to easily handle string replacements based on a regular expression.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IPatternTokenizer
files.Summary: A tokenizer of type pattern that can flexibly separate text into terms via a regular expression.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IPercolateQuery
files.Summary: The percolate query can be used to match queries stored in an index

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IPercolatorProperty
files.Summary: The percolator datatype is used to store a query, so that the can use it to match provided documents.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IPhoneticTokenFilter
files.Summary: A token filter that converts tokens to their phonetic representation using Soundex, Metaphone, and a variety of other algorithms.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IPhraseSuggestCollate
files.Summary: Checks each suggestion against the specified query to prune suggestions for which no matching docs exist in the index.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IPhraseSuggestCollateQuery
files.Summary: A query to run for a phrase suggester collate

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IPhraseSuggester
files.Summary: The phrase suggester adds additional logic on top of the to select entire corrected phrases instead of individual tokens weighted based on ngram-language models. In practice this suggester will be able to make better decisions about which tokens to pick based on co-occurrence and frequencies.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IPorterStemTokenFilter
files.Summary: A token filter of type porterStem that transforms the token stream as per the Porter stemming algorithm.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IPredicateTokenFilter
files.Summary: The predicate_token_filter token filter takes a predicate script, and removes tokens that do not match the predicate.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IProcessor
files.Summary: Ingest pipelines are composed of one or more processors

files.Summary: A mapping for a property type to a document field in OpenSearch

files.Summary: Determines how a POCO property maps to the property on a JSON object when serialized

files.Summary: A mapping for a property from a CLR type

files.Summary: A request that that does not necessarily (de)serializes itself

files.Summary: A request to put an alias to one or more indices

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IQueryStringQuery
files.Summary: A query that uses a query parser in order to parse its content

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IRankFeatureFunction
files.Summary: A function to boost scores in a rank_feature query, using the values of rank features.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IRankFeatureLinearFunction
files.Summary:
Gives a score equal to the indexed value of S, where S is the value of the rank feature field.

If a rank feature field is indexed with "positive_score_impact": true, its indexed value is equal to S and rounded to preserve only 9 significant bits for the precision.

If a rank feature field is indexed with "positive_score_impact": false, its indexed value is equal to 1/S and rounded to preserve only 9 significant bits for the precision.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IRankFeatureLogarithmFunction
files.Summary: Gives a score that is equal to log(scaling_factor + S) where S is the value of the rank feature and scaling_factor is a configurable scaling factor. Scores are unbounded. This function only supports rank features that have a positive score impact.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IRankFeatureProperty
files.Summary: A field that can index numbers so that they can later be used to boost documents in queries with a rank_feature query.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IRankFeatureQuery
files.Summary:
A query that only works on rank_feature fields and rank_features fields. Its goal is to boost the score of documents based on the values of numeric features. It is typically put in a should clause of a bool query so that its score is added to the score of the query.

Compared to using function_score or other ways to modify the score, this query has the benefit of being able to efficiently skip non-competitive hits when track_total_hits is not set to true. Speedups may be spectacular.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IRankFeatureSaturationFunction
files.Summary: Gives a score that is equal to S / (S + pivot) where S is the value of the rank feature and pivot is a configurable pivot value so that the result will be less than 0.5 if S is less than pivot and greater than 0.5 otherwise. Scores are always is (0, 1). If the rank feature has a negative score impact then the function will be computed as pivot / (S + pivot), which decreases when S increases.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IRankFeatureSigmoidFunction
files.Summary:
is an extension of saturation which adds a configurable exponent. Scores are computed as S^exp^ / (S^exp^ + pivot^exp^). Like for the saturation function, pivot is the value of S that gives a score of 0.5 and scores are in (0, 1).

exponent must be positive, but is typically in [0.5, 1]. A good value should be computed via training. If you dont have the opportunity to do so, we recommend that you stick to the saturation function instead.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IRankFeaturesProperty
files.Summary: A field that can index numeric feature vectors, so that they can later be used to boost documents in queries with a rank_feature query. It is analogous to the datatype, but is better suited when the list of features is sparse so that it wouldn't be reasonable to add one field to the mappings for each of them.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IRareTermsAggregation
files.Summary: A multi-bucket value source based aggregation which finds "rare" terms  terms that are at the long-tail of the distribution and are not frequent. Conceptually, this is like a terms aggregation that is sorted by _count ascending.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IReadOnlyUrlRepository
files.Summary: A snapshot repository that can be used as an alternative read-only way to access data created by the . The URL specified in the url parameter should point to the root of the shared filesystem repository.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IRegexpQuery
files.Summary: Queries documents that contain terms matching a regular expression.

files.Summary: Configures the source for a reindex API request

files.Summary: A token filter that drops identical tokens at the same position

files.Summary: Removes existing fields. If one field doesn't exist, an exception will be thrown.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IRenameProcessor

files.Summary: A snapshot repository with typed settings

files.Summary: A request to the resolve index API

files.Summary: A token filter of type reverse that simply reverses the tokens.

files.Summary: Conditions that must be satisfied for a new index to be created with the rollover index API

files.Summary:
A snapshot repository that stores snapshots in an Amazon S3 bucket

Requires the repository-s3 plugin to be installed on the cluster

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IScript
files.Summary: A script to execute to provide custom computation

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IScriptProcessor
files.Summary: Allows inline and stored scripts to be executed within ingest pipelines.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IScriptQuery
files.Summary: A query allowing to define a script to execute as a query

files.Summary: The script score function allows you to wrap another query and customize the scoring of it optionally with a computation derived from other numeric field values in the doc using a script expression.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ISearchAsYouTypeProperty
files.Summary:
A text-like field that is optimized to provide out-of-the-box support for the "search as you type" completion use case.

It creates a series of subfields that are analyzed to index terms that can be efficiently matched by a query that partially matches the entire indexed text value. Both prefix completion (i.e matching terms starting at the beginning of the input) and infix completion (i.e. matching terms at any position within the input) are supported.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ISearchResponse<TDocument>
files.Summary: A response to a search request

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ISetProcessor
files.Summary: Sets one field and associates it with the specified value. If the field already exists, its value will be replaced with the provided one.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.IShingleTokenFilter
files.Summary:
A token filter of type shingle that constructs shingles (token n-grams) from a token stream.

In other words, it creates combinations of tokens as a single token.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ISignificantTextAggregation
files.Summary: An aggregation that returns interesting or unusual occurrences of free-text terms in a set.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ISimpleAnalyzer
files.Summary: An analyzer of type simple that is built using a Lower Case Tokenizer.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ISimpleQueryStringQuery
files.Summary: A query that uses the SimpleQueryParser to parse its context. Unlike the regular , the query will never throw an exception, and discards invalid parts of the query.

files.Title: OpenSearch.Client.ISnowballAnalyzer

Median absolute deviation is a measure of variability. It is a robust statistic, meaning that it is useful for describing data that may have outliers, or may not be normally distributed. For such data it can be more descriptive than standard deviation.

X
